    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="866"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d866">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751.90D11/10–944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Appointed Minister to Syria and Lebanon</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-09T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 9, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 9—3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>216. I hesitate to make verbal statement suggested in Department’s 177, October
                    7, 7 [<hi rend="italic">9</hi>] p.m.<note n="68" xml:id="d866fn68">Not
                        printed.</note> prior to learning something of Syrian Government reaction to
                    Eden reply (Legtel 213, October 6, 8 p.m.) which is to be handed Foreign
                    Minister this week.</p>
                <p>May I not therefore when presenting reply outlined in Department’s 176 October 7,
                    8 p.m. limit my remarks to inquiry as to whether the Minister believes more
                    favorable terms could be obtained now than later.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
